    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "Redescription of Astyanax gymnogenys Eigenmann, 1911 (Characiformes Characidae), a senior synonym of Astyanax longirhinus Garavello & Sampaio 2010" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449301>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449303> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449301>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Astyanax gymmogenys, all from Brazil, Paraná State, rio Iguaçu basin: (a) FMNH 54707, holotype of A. gymnogenys, 64.9 mm SL, middle rio Iguaçu, Porto União. (b) FMNH 54708, paratype of A. gymnogenys, 65.1 mm SL, same locality of holotype. (c) NUP 17522, 67.1 mm SL, topotype. (d) NUP 11290, 79.9 mm SL; (e) NUP 11290, 82.6 mm SL; (f) NUP 11290, 109.9 mm SL, lower rio Iguaçu in Salto Santiago reservoir, Foz do Jordão. (g) MZUSP 105954, holotype of A. longirhinus, 151.5 mm SL, lower rio Iguaçu downstream from Salto Santiago reservoir, Laranjeiras do Sul." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3449301/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3449303>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Map of southeast South America showing the geographic distribution of Astyanax gymnogenys. Yellow star indicates the type-locality of A. gymnogenys, red star indicates the type-locality of A. longirhinus, and yellow dots remaining known localities for the species. “A” and “B” indicate the limits of upper and middle rio Iguaçu basin, respectively, according to Ingenito et al. (2004)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3449303/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

